					<head>Commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>A fragment of an anonymous commentary on the Former Prophets.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="57v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פירוש</title>
							<note>
								<p>Many explanations of terms are given in an old French (12th century) see 4r, 16r, 19r, 21v.</p>
							</note>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="3r" to="10v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Joshua</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="10v" to="22v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Judges</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="22v" to="27r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Samuel</title>
								<note>
									<p>Only three folios with the commentary on 1Samuel and one folio on 2Samuel are preserved, folios 22v-27r.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="27r" to="55r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Kings</title>
								<note>
									<p>2Kings begin on folio 43r.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper and vellum codex, Sefardi (Provencal) semi-cursive script, unpunctuated, of 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="mixed">
								<support>Mixed paper and vellum.</support>
								<extent rend="visible">57 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>305</height>
										<width>210</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>215</height>
										<width>140</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>57 folios (+ 4 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Irregular number of leaves in the quire.</p>
									<p>Folios 1-2 and 56-57 constitute one large folio each, folded in two.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Has lacunae after folios: 10, 17, 21, 25, 26, 31, 46, 47, 50, 54.</p>
									<p>Partially water-damaged. Several stains.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout ruledLines="25" writtenLines="25" columns="1">
									<p>One column, 25 regular lines.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi (Provencal) semi-cursive script, unpunctuated, of 14th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folios 1r-2v and 56r-57v contain a notarial instrument of Bertrand de Rua of Toulouse, regarding debts held by various people towards Master Salomon Mosse, dated 7 December 1383 and 3 June 1383 respectively.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Elia Lattas</name>: inscribed with a date of <date calendar="Gregorian">17 August 1590</date>, folio 3r. </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Fr. Alexander Longus Inquisitore de Montis regalis</name>: inscribed, folio 3r.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM/BL in-house. </p>
								<p>Boxed.</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
